          <declname>id</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>std::string</type>
          <declname>dataSource</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Compares the list of files assigned to the running process by the<verbatim>embed:rst:inline :doc:`assignment-creation` </verbatim> protocol and those within the<verbatim>embed:rst:inline :ref:`stellar-directory` </verbatim>. If there is a match (which there <bold>really</bold> should be), it returns the assigned file objects as a list <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The MPI id of the running process, a number between 0 and NProcesses - 1 </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dataSource</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The directory in which the stellar data is stored </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A list of the <ref refid="structFile" kindref="compound">File</ref> objects assigned to this process </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
